reviews.review_text: First Show ! This was my first show and It sure didn't seem like anyone left this show disappointed and I surely didn't hear anybody saying ah '88 isn't that great . The only thing about 1988 was Jerry's vocals sounded winded a lot of times but he still gave it his all on  "goodbye momma and poppa...".. and "wish I was a headlight ..And they were running the vocals pretty dry aside from occasional chipmunk vocalizer from Healy , I went to this show totally sober and it was like my body was dancing whether I wanted to or not , and I wasn't a dancer and was shy ,but I already had like 500 tapes by this show ,so to finally to be able to see my favorite band , it was unthinkable to me at the time that it might not be a great show and this probably is my favorite tape from '88 now , 9/12/88 is pretty awesome..Thank you all involved in making this copy available. the ultra -matrix sounds more like it did than the dry soundboard... Don't let hearing a show  or whole year of shows is no good make you just skip over it  . I like to think more positive as there are gems every year ,and whether or not a show is good or bad is subjective in the first place. To me everytime they broke down the equipment and set it back up in a different place with different acoustics made  each show that much more unique tp itself . I'm glad they weren't trying to sound like 1970 or 1977 etc.. It was like a living giant in the moment unique like a thumbprint
